#### 5. Minimum quantitative gain threshold

- `[VERIFIED]` The local record does not support a sharper numeric threshold.
- `[INFERRED]` The minimum meaningful threshold still visible on disk is:
  a strictly positive, one-sided improvement on the named stretching/enstrophy bad term or forbidden transfer pattern that still survives mixed-helicity restoration, low-helicity regions, pressure, viscosity, and localization on a quantitatively relevant burden share.
- Support:
